.TH AMSFTP 1
.SH NAME
amsftp \- Vim-first two-pane SFTP commander
.SH SYNOPSIS
.TP
\fBamsftp [<location> [<location>]]\fR
Open the two-pane client with zero, one, or two locations.
.TP
\fBamsftp --workspace <name>\fR
Open a saved workspace.
.TP
\fBamsftp daemon <start|status> [--format human|json] | amsftp daemon stop --confirm stop [--format human|json]\fR
Start, inspect, or explicitly stop the local daemon.
.TP
\fBamsftp job <list|events|pause|resume|cancel> [arguments]\fR
Query or control durable Jobs through the local daemon; cancellation requires exact Job ID confirmation.
.TP
\fBamsftp helper <status|disable> <SSH-host> [--format human|json] | amsftp helper <install|upgrade|remove> <SSH-host> --accept-shared-session-stable-home [--format human|json]\fR
Inspect or disable Helper state, or request release-admitted install/upgrade/exact removal; lifecycle remains fail-closed until protected composition exists.
.TP
\fBamsftp config <validate|print-effective|print-effective-keymap|reset-keymap> [arguments]\fR
Validate configuration, print versioned effective output, or explicitly reset keymap overrides.
.TP
\fBamsftp doctor [--endpoint <SSH-host>] [--format human|json]\fR
Run bounded read-only local checks and optionally test one SSH endpoint without prompting for credentials.
.TP
\fBamsftp upgrade [--format human|json]\fR
Upgrade a Homebrew or standalone macOS/Linux installation and safely preserve daemon state.
.TP
\fBamsftp support-bundle preview [--format human|json] | amsftp support-bundle create --consent <sha256> --output <absolute-path> [--format human|json]\fR
Preview the exact reviewed diagnostic archive, then explicitly publish it to a private no-replace local file.
.TP
\fBamsftp completion <bash|zsh|fish>\fR
Print a shell completion script with saved-workspace completion.
.TP
\fBamsftp [client|askpass|helper] [arguments...]\fR
Run an explicit client or restricted internal role.
.TP
\fBamsftp --help\fR
Print command help.
.TP
\fBamsftp --version\fR
Print version and build information.
.SH DESCRIPTION
AMSFTP delegates SSH authentication and host policy to the validated system OpenSSH, keeps standard SFTP as the baseline, and requires explicit confirmation for destructive operations.
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 success; 1 internal; 2 usage; 3 configuration; 4 authentication; 5 network; 6 conflict; 7 partial completion; 8 user cancellation.
.SH FILES
See the AMSFTP configuration reference for platform paths, schema version, precedence, and redaction.
